data.chText: 英联邦（由英国和大多数曾经隶属于大英帝国的国家组成）
data.enText: an organization consisting of the United Kingdom and most of the countries that used to be part of the British Empire

data.chText: （用于美国肯塔基、马萨诸塞、宾夕法尼亚和弗吉尼亚四州的正式名称中）州
data.enText: used in the official names of, and to refer to, some states of the US (Kentucky, Massachusetts, Pennsylvania and Virginia)

data.chText: 这座城市和这个州失去了一位伟大的领袖。
data.enText: The city and the Commonwealth have lost a great leader.

data.chText: （与美国联系紧密的）自治政区
data.enText: an independent country that is strongly connected to the US

data.chText: 波多黎各至今仍然是美国的一个自治政区，而不是一个州。
data.enText: Puerto Rico remains a US commonwealth, not a state.

data.chText: （用于某些政治上相互有联系的国家集团的名称）联合体
data.enText: used in the names of some groups of countries or states that have chosen to be politically linked with each other

data.chText: 独立国家联合体（独联体）

means: 英联邦(由英国和大多数曾经隶属于大英帝国的国家组成)
(用于美国肯塔基、马萨诸塞、宾夕法尼亚和弗吉尼亚四州的正式名称中)州
(与美国联系紧密的)自治政区

tr: a politically organized body of people under a single government
example: the state has elected a new president
students who had come to the nation's capitol

tr: a political system in which the supreme power lies in a body of citizens who can elect people to represent them
a world organization of autonomous states that are united in allegiance to a central power but are not subordinate to it or to one another
the official name of some states in the United States (Massachusetts and Pennsylvania and Virginia and Kentucky) and associated territories (Puerto Rico)

value.def: The Commonwealth is an organization consisting of the United Kingdom and most of the countries that were previously under its rule.
Commonwealth is used in the official names of some countries, groups of countries, or parts of countries.

example.ex: ...the Commonwealth of Independent States, which replaced the Soviet Union.
example.tran: 取代了苏联的独立国家联合体

value.tran: 联邦，联合体(用于正式名称中)

value.def: If you refer to a commonwealth of nations, you are referring to a group of countries who are friendly towards each other and have something in common.

example.ex: ...a commonwealth of nations without economic borders.
example.tran: 经济上自由往来的几个国家组成的联盟

value.tran: (关系友好、有共同点的国家组成的)团体
